Commands to run:

1) 
Run the following command
	export PATH=$PATH:/Applications/Postgres.app/Contents/Versions/10/bin
	# The number 10 here refers to the version number
in the folder 
	/Applications/Postgres.app/Contents/Versions/10/bin
after starting the Postgres server and having it running. On a MacOS, it can be done using the application 
	http://postgresapp.com/

2)
Navigate to the project folder 
	cd course_management_system/
Activate the virtual enviroment using
	source cms/bin/activate
If any changes have been made to the project, then run the following two commands:
	python manage.py makemigrations
	python manage.py migrate
If there were no changes made, then running the first command should say "No changes detected".
Once you see that, run the following 
	python manage.py runserver
The above commands runs the server at the following URL
	http://127.0.0.1:8000/
In order to access the admin page use the URL below
	http://127.0.0.1:8000/admin


Superuser account details are:
	Username: admin
	Email address: cmsadmin@gmail.com
	pwd: cmspwdt12


